  As Table 1.4.1 indicates, agricultural land represents 13 
percent of all land resources (222.3 million* hectares). 
  Figure 1.4.1 illustrates the share of total land resources 
occupied by plowed fields. 


<FIG ID=JPRS-TEN-005-28A>           Figure 1.4.1. Percentage of Total </FIG>



  The area of agricultural land decreased by 12.4 million* 
hectares in the last 27 years, including a decrease of 2.3 
million* hectares in plowed fields and 10.6 million* hectares in 
hayfields. The reasons for the reduction of agricultural area 
are the destruction and degradation of topsoil and the inclusion 
of some agricultural land in the territory of cities, 
settlements, and industrial enterprises. 
  Changes in the plowed area in different parts of the Russian 
Federation are presented in Figure 1.4.2. 


<FIG ID=JPRS-TEN-005-28B>           Figure 1.4.2. Changes in 1992 Plowed </FIG>



  Russia's chernozem soils cover an area of around 120 million 
hectares. This is only around 7 percent of the total area, but 
this is the location of more than half of all the plowed fields 
and the source of around 80 percent of all farming products. 
  The distribution of agricultural soils is presented in Table 
1.4.2. 


Table 1.4.2. Structure of Soil Cover of Agricultural Land of Russian 
Federation (percentage of total area) 

