  Forest fires are still causing colossal damage to forests 
(Table 1.6.3). The area consumed by these fires has recently 
exceeded a million hectares a year, and in 1992 it totaled 1.143 
million* hectares, exceeding the 1991 area by 17,000* hectares. 


Table 1.6.3. Forest Fires in Russian Federation 

             Area consumed by fire,        Total damage, millions of rubles 
             thousands of ha 

Years        Total          Densely        Reported        Estimated** 
                            wooded 

1988         1012.8*        758.7*         88.7*           56812.5* 

1989         2056.5*        1511.2*        202.0*          112822.5* 

